"""
era_babel_rebellion.py -- The Third Rebellion: Babel (Chapters 5-6)

The third rebellion is the most consequential for understanding the
current state of the world. At Babel (Genesis 11), God scattered the
nations and -- according to Deuteronomy 32:8-9 (DSS/LXX reading) --
assigned them to the 'sons of God' (bene elohim / huioi theou), divine
beings tasked with governing the scattered peoples. God kept Israel
for himself: 'For YHWH's portion is his people, Jacob his allotted
heritage' (32:9). Those delegates failed catastrophically. Psalm 82
records the divine courtroom where God fires them: 'I said, You are
gods (elohim), sons of the Most High, all of you; nevertheless, like
men you shall die, and fall like any prince.'

The Deuteronomy 32 worldview is the key to understanding territorial
spiritual conflict, the distinction between Israel and the nations,
and why Christ's work at Pentecost specifically reverses Babel.
"""

